 # Flaky jj test cleanup: rm -rf intermittently fails in afterEach
 
-
+The jj backend integration tests in storage-cmd.test.ts use execSync('rm -rf "${rootDir}"') in afterEach to clean up jj workspace directories (Node's rmSync fails on macOS with jj's .jj/ structure). This cleanup intermittently fails with 'Command failed: rm -rf ...' when run in the full test suite (parallel execution), though tests pass individually.
+
+Likely cause: jj's workspace background processes or file locks haven't released by the time afterEach runs when other test files are executing concurrently.
+
+Options:
+1. Add a short delay before cleanup
+2. Use vitest's --no-file-parallelism for this test file
+3. Wrap rm -rf in a retry loop
+4. Accept the flakiness (it only affects cleanup, not test assertions)
+
